Heat olive oil and 1 teaspoon butter in a skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir mushrooms in butter until tender and browned, about 10 minutes. Stir cooked mushrooms, potatoes, Cheddar cheese, milk, onion, 2 tablespoons butter, garlic salt, and black pepper together in a slow cooker. Cook on High until potatoes are tender and Cheddar cheese is melted, about 4 hours.